('chk-portfolio-capstone', 'ph-portfolio-capstone', 90, 'checkpoint', 'review', NULL, NULL, 'Portfolio, Interview Readiness, and Capstone Review Checkpoint', 'Final roadmap checkpoint for Portfolio, Interview Readiness, and Capstone. The learner reviews portfolio evidence, unresolved gaps, and next learning priorities across the full-stack engineering path.', 'This checkpoint closes the suggested full-stack engineering orientation path by organizing evidence and next steps. It is not an employment guarantee or formal competency certification.', 'checkpoint', 'ph-portfolio-capstone', 14, 90, 2, 'advanced', 95, NULL, NULL, '{"source": "platform-generated", "checkpointType": "review", "checkpointPurpose": "phase_review", "reviewMode": "final_review", "evidenceRequired": true, "claimLimit": "orientation_and_progress_review_only_not_certification"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Connect completed roadmap work to a coherent full-stack engineering learning narrative.", "Review portfolio or project evidence and identify which artifacts are ready to share.", "Define remaining gaps and future specialization priorities."]'::jsonb, '["Summarize completed phases, projects, and major skill groups.", "Attach or reference portfolio evidence, project links, diagrams, reports, tests, or notes where available.", "List remaining gaps or specialization topics for future learning.", "State that the checkpoint is a planning review, not proof of job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('proj-fullstack-capstone', 'ph-portfolio-capstone', 101, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Full Stack Capstone Project', 'Capstone project: Build a portfolio-grade full stack application with polished frontend UX, backend API, database, authentication, testing, deployment, monitoring notes, and a case study.', 'This project gives learners a concrete way to practice Portfolio, Interview Readiness, and Capstone by producing a portfolio-ready Full Stack Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact. The artifact is intended for review and reflection, not as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 'side', 'ph-portfolio-capstone', 14, 101, 18, 'advanced', 100, NULL, NULL, '{"project":true,"projectBrief":"Build a portfolio-grade full stack application with polished frontend UX, backend API, database, authentication, testing, deployment, monitoring notes, and a case study.","projectKind":"portfolio_capstone","projectScope":"portfolio_capstone","projectPurpose":"Integrate several roadmap areas into a portfolio-ready case study.","phaseContext":"Portfolio, Interview Readiness, and Capstone","deliverable":"a portfolio-ready Full Stack Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact","skillsToPractice":["Full Stack Development","API","React","SQL","Portfolio Communication"],"suggestedSteps":["Define the Full Stack Capstone Project scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: API behavior, monitoring signals, UI flow.","Choose a coherent product or case-study scenario that can integrate the strongest projects from the roadmap.","Define the architecture, data or workflow model, user path, and review evidence before implementation.","Build the core artifact end-to-end with scoped features rather than disconnected demos.","Add validation evidence appropriate to the role, such as tests, metrics, query checks, playtest notes, traces, screenshots, or incident notes.","Prepare a case study explaining decisions, trade-offs, limitations, and what would need further review for real deployment.","Package the repository or artifact so another person can reproduce or inspect the result.","Create a review checklist that connects the artifact to the relevant skills and roadmap segment.","Write a limitation and risk section so the project is presented as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"expectedEvidence":["a portfolio-ready Full Stack Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact.","README or notes that explain setup, usage, assumptions, and expected output.","Case study page or write-up that connects the artifact to role-relevant decisions and evidence.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement.","Architecture, review checklist, and limitation section suitable for portfolio discussion."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":false,"milestone":true,"source":"platform-generated","nodeKey":"proj-fullstack-capstone"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Full Stack Development, API, React through a focused Full Stack Capstone Project artifact.","Integrate multiple roadmap areas into one coherent case study rather than isolated exercises.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a portfolio-ready Full Stack Capstone Project case study and integrated artifact is available for review.","The Full Stack Capstone Project scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","The case study connects implementation decisions to relevant roadmap skills and explains why alternatives were not chosen.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness.","The project is packaged so a reviewer can understand the artifact without live mentoring."]'::jsonb),
('proj-open-source-or-team-contribution', 'ph-portfolio-capstone', 102, 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional Open Source or Team Contribution', 'Capstone project: Contribute a bug fix, documentation improvement, test, component, or feature to an existing project and document the collaboration process.', 'This project gives learners a concrete way to practice Portfolio, Interview Readiness, and Capstone by producing a portfolio-ready Open Source or Team Contribution case study and integrated artifact. The artifact is intended for review and reflection, not as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 'side', 'ph-portfolio-capstone', 14, 102, 6, 'advanced', 60, NULL, NULL, '{"project":true,"projectBrief":"Contribute a bug fix, documentation improvement, test, component, or feature to an existing project and document the collaboration process.","projectKind":"portfolio_capstone","projectScope":"portfolio_capstone","projectPurpose":"Integrate several roadmap areas into a portfolio-ready case study.","phaseContext":"Portfolio, Interview Readiness, and Capstone","deliverable":"a portfolio-ready Open Source or Team Contribution case study and integrated artifact","skillsToPractice":["Portfolio Communication"],"suggestedSteps":["Define the Open Source or Team Contribution scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: test evidence.","Choose a coherent product or case-study scenario that can integrate the strongest projects from the roadmap.","Define the architecture, data or workflow model, user path, and review evidence before implementation.","Build the core artifact end-to-end with scoped features rather than disconnected demos.","Add validation evidence appropriate to the role, such as tests, metrics, query checks, playtest notes, traces, screenshots, or incident notes.","Prepare a case study explaining decisions, trade-offs, limitations, and what would need further review for real deployment.","Package the repository or artifact so another person can reproduce or inspect the result.","Create a review checklist that connects the artifact to the relevant skills and roadmap segment.","Write a limitation and risk section so the project is presented as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"expectedEvidence":["a portfolio-ready Open Source or Team Contribution case study and integrated artifact.","README or notes that explain setup, usage, assumptions, and expected output.","Case study page or write-up that connects the artifact to role-relevant decisions and evidence.","Validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, query results, metrics, traces, or review notes.","Short reflection on trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement.","Architecture, review checklist, and limitation section suitable for portfolio discussion."],"reviewFocus":["Does the artifact directly match the project brief?","Can another person run, inspect, or review the result from the provided notes?","Are assumptions, limitations, and trade-offs stated clearly?"],"scopeGuardrails":["Keep the implementation focused on the stated project brief.","Prefer a complete small artifact over a broad unfinished system.","Treat completion as reviewable evidence, not a certification claim."],"claimLimit":"Completion creates reviewable project evidence. It does not certify mastery or guarantee job readiness.","evidenceRequired":true,"optionalPractice":true,"milestone":false,"source":"platform-generated","nodeKey":"proj-open-source-or-team-contribution"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Portfolio Communication through a focused Open Source or Team Contribution artifact.","Integrate multiple roadmap areas into one coherent case study rather than isolated exercises.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a portfolio-ready Open Source or Team Contribution case study and integrated artifact is available for review.","The Open Source or Team Contribution scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","The case study connects implementation decisions to relevant roadmap skills and explains why alternatives were not chosen.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness.","The project is packaged so a reviewer can understand the artifact without live mentoring."]'::jsonb)
